Demonstrate your understanding of this Sprint's concepts by answering the following free-form questions. Edit the `ANSWERS.md` file to include your answers after each question. Make sure to leave a blank line above and below your answer so it is clear and easy to read by your project manager.

- [ ] Why would you use class component over function components (removing hooks from the question)?

A difference is the ability to create custom hooks, you can use state easier and differently due to this.state. Also the use of event handling can be used in multiple ways.
after using class components you have to render something, this gives you a chance to console log for debugging, and determining State at that point.

- [ ] Name three lifecycle methods and their purposes.

componentDidMount- Runs as a method to give some task once whateverver component is mounted or actioned... such as an API working.
componentWillReceiveProps- a mthos tat runs when a component runs props
getSnapShotBeforeUpdate- before updating state, this method creates a backup of the way things are Currently.

- [ ] What is the purpose of a custom hook?

The purpose of custome hooks are to allow us to extract component logic into reusable functions. Helps with sharing stateful logic with adding excessive components.

- [ ] Why is it important to test our apps?

The inportance of testing our apps is to ensure they are functioning properly and doing what they are expected to do (Quality Check).